    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n- No easy way to download a file, though both `curl` and libuv are available in all Nvim targets.\n- `:edit <uri>` (example: `:edit https://example.com/foo.txt`) is dependent on netrw for no reason\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nseparate PRs:\n\n* [x] introduce `vim.net.request()` (`vim.net.fetch()` ? idk, look at Go, NodeJS, for precedent)\n    - could use `curl` or `vim.uv`\n* [x] use it to implement `:edit <uri>` without netrw\n* [Â ] use it to implement spellfile download. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/7189\n\n\n### Related\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/23231\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/4378\n\n### Use-cases in the wild\n\n- https://github.com/3rd/image.nvim/blob/88e9693e188b8464b1c426aebb4389fd9db2fcbf/lua/image/image.lua#L393",
